				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Hot Spots Discussion<a name="37052"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 28 04 1:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>From 4.28.2004 Patch Message
<br />
--------------
<br />

<br />
Hot Spots 
<br />
----------------------- 
<br />
Try out the new Hot Spot zones which give a boost to Experience while adventuring in them, in a similar manner to Paludal Caverns. The current Hot Spots are: 
<br />

<br />
- The Castle of Mistmoore (20th to 30th level) 
<br />
- The Lair of the Splitpaw (35th to 45th level) 
<br />
- Dulak's Harbor (40th to 45th level) 
<br />
- The Tower of Frozen Shadow (30th to 35th level) 
<br />
- The Gulf of Gunthak (35th to 40th level) 
<br />
- Hate's Fury (55th to 60th level) 
<br />
- The Crypt of Nadox (50th to 55th level) 
<br />
- The Torgiran Mines (45th to 50th level) 
<br />

<br />
These Hot Spot zones are generally aimed at characters level 20 to 51. The Hot Spot zones will shift from time to time, so watch for messages giving clues as to where the new ones may be. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
-------
<br />

<br />
Anyone played around in these hot spots yet? Is the exp bonus noticeable? Please note your char level &amp; which zone!
<br />

<br />
Also, for all those above 60 - will we get the exp bonus in these zones (particularly Hate's Fury), or does the level restriction strictly mean only that range of characters will gain bonus exp.
<br />

<br />
I am wavering between the level range given meaning
<br />
  1) the level of the mobs that give bonus exp, or
<br />
  2) the level the characters need to be to get bonus exp
<br />

<br />
In the case of (1) above, then Hate's Fury may be good exp for 60-65s. If (2) then it obviously will not have changed.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the discussion  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
