				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hot Spots Discussion<a name="37157"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 29 04 12:12 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My Opinion is that the Hot spot is for certain levels of character in those zones.  I dinged my Monk to level 35 tonight, and got a big a$ obnoxious popup box telling me to go to Gunthak.  Didn't have time to read it (which is annoying) as I was pulling and LDoN at the time but it repeated Gunthak, like 8 times in 5 lines, at least.
<br />

<br />
My interpretation was that they were telling me, &quot;now that you are 35 you will get more XP in Gunthak, so go there... NOW! Quick! before you level beyond the Hot Spot&quot;  While the ZEMs are indeed coded zone wide, I can think of a couple different ways they could make the XP dependant on the levels of the players killing, and coding in a modifier depending on whether in a certain level range or not.
<br />

<br />
It is interesting that they are doing this after all the Fabled camps.  Looks like they realized that there is indeed value in spreading out the population a bit more, and this is one way they want to do it.  Makes for less stress on the servers handling certain popular zones making the system as a whole more stable.  Like others have said, these are all severely underused zones, and we will probably be seeing it move to, others in the months to come.  I am thinking of Cazic, Feerot, Lake Rathe, and City of Mist, for example.  By focusing on certain levels for these zones they force people to different zones, even though they are good for more levels then that range listed.
<br />

<br />
Tenosh on Prexus.</span></td>
